    TensorFlow Java Parent 1.2.0-SNAPSHOT API

    TensorFlow-Java provides a Java API for TensorFlow, wrapped around TensorFlow's C API. It allows the training and deployment of models using TensorFlow, with a focus on serving models trained using other TensorFlow APIs.

    It is split into 4 modules:

    • tensorflow - The core TF-Java module which provides functionality for loading, saving and deploying TensorFlow models, along with Java definitions of all TensorFlow operators.
    • tensorflow.framework - Higher level framework functionality for optimizers, losses, metrics etc.
    • tensorflow.generator - Java side op generation code from TensorFlow's op definition protobufs.
    • tensorflow.native - The low level Java - C API binding.

    TensorFlow-Java is developed in the open on GitHub by members of the TensorFlow community.

    Modules
    Module
    Description
    tensorflow
    Core module implementing the TensorFlow Java API and operator definitions.
    tensorflow.framework
    Higher level TensorFlow framework containing model definition and training operations.
    tensorflow.generator
    Code to generate the Java side implementations of TensorFlow's ops based on the TensorFlow op definition files.
    tensorflow.nativelib
    Native interop with the TensorFlow C API.
